Kaietur International Airport (IATA: KIA, ICAO: PSKA) is the national airport of the [[Potaro-Siparuni]] region and is the second largest gateway to [[Guyana]]. 

== Airlines and Destinations ==

*[[Trans Guyana Airways]] (Georgetown)
*[[Roraima Airways]] (Georgetown)
*[[XL Airways]] (London-Gatwick)
*[[Rutaca]] (Caracas)

== Runways ==

Kaieteur currently has 1 runway at 9, 600 ft.
